A little gin cocktail can spice up your taste buds, especially with this Nairobi heat. Nothing but a cold berry gin on ice. Gin is actually one of the healthiest spirits that have ever been created. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Put ice cubes in a balloon glass Step 2 Add gin, lime juice, blueberry juice and a few ice cubes in a shaker, add Schweppes and shake for a minute. Step 3 Pour the mixture over ice cubes in the glass and garnish with mint and blueberries. Enjoy the sweet fruity drink with friends and family.